    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.22.1-2_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">1</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Z&#252;rich 57. 4. 4. 48
                        Seminarstr. 97
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                            <addrLine>New-York.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Sir:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I was just reading your book "Black Elk Speaks", lent by a friend, who himself don't could buy it, not finding a copy available. As we are very interested in all concerning the Tetons we sea<add>r</add>ched for the book, still now without success. May I disturb you with the question if I could buy one or two copies directly from you?</p>
                
                <p>My friend speaks Lakota and is able to write to acquainted members of the Ogalalas. For myself I wrote often articles about Indian matters, men, tribes, their history, museums pieces etc. Therefore we thank you for your writing down of Black Elks history and its printing, hoping that his vision will find a sort of realisation, whilst just now a part of the tribe seems to come to his self-consciousness.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very truly yours,</salute>
                    <signed>Gottfr. Hotz</signed>
                    <signed>(Gottfr. Hotz)</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.22.1-2_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">2</fw>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    Ein Tagesverdiensl
                    f&#252;r die
                    hungernden Kinder
                    SCHWEIZER EUROPAHILFE
                
                    ZURICH
                    8-9
                    <unclear/>
                    1948
                    UNIVERSAND
                </ab>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>40            Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>40 HELVETIA</p>
                </figure>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine><del>p.r. address: William Morrow &amp; Co. Editors</del></addrLine>
                
                        <addrLine><del>423 Fourth Ave.</del></addrLine>
                        <addrLine><del>New York 16, N.Y.</del></addrLine>
